  "text": "It is usually assumed that a lower proportion of planted canola seed will become seedlings. [CITATION_1] studies suggests that 50% emergence is a representative average of canola emergence under field conditions. Furthermore, differences between target and actual densities demonstrated that percent germination (greater than 90% for the seed used in this study) greatly overestimates the number of plants that actually emerge under field conditions. According to [CITATION_2] , typical seeding rates for canola in Western Canada would be close to 100 seeds m -2 (5.5 kg ha -1",
